    },
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nThe `Painter` needs to paint another diagonal line! This time from the top right to the bottom left!\r\n- In your `custom.py` file, create the `paint_diagonal(color)` function definition with the needed `if` statements and ***nested*** `if` statements within it. \r\n\r\n**Reminder:** Make sure you import your `custom.py` file and save it to your backpack after adding any new functions!\r\n\r\n---\r\n## AI Tutor Support\r\n- If you're unsure **how to check when the Painter should paint and move,** use AI Tutor to explore how conditionals affect movement.\r\n- If you're **having trouble making the diagonal line continue correctly,** ask AI for debugging help.\r\n\r\n",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n# ADD import custom BELOW\n\n\n# Create Painter object\nsergio = Painter()\n\n# Function to move while can\ndef move_while_can():\n  while sergio.can_move():\n    sergio.move()\n\n# Function to take all the paint\ndef take_all_paint():\n  while sergio.is_on_bucket():\n    sergio.take_paint()\n\n# Function definition for turn right\ndef turn_right():\n  sergio.turn_left()\n  sergio.turn_left()\n  sergio.turn_left()\n\n# Function to turn around\ndef turn_around():\n  sergio.turn_left()\n  sergio.turn_left()\n\n# ADD DEFINITION FOR paint_diagonal(color) FUNCTION IN custom.py\n        \n\n# Call functions here\nmove_while_can()\ntake_all_paint()\nturn_around()\ncustom.paint_diagonal(\"pink\")\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": false,
          "open": true,
          "type": "locked_starter"
        }
      },
